The problem requires finding the kth smallest number in the range [1, n]. We can solve this by iterating k times and multiplying n and dividing by (n + 1) in each iteration. This ensures that the result will be the kth smallest number. The time complexity is O(k) since we perform k iterations. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the result variable. The energy implications are low because the algorithm has a simple iteration process and does not require any complex data structures or operations.

